<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="384" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,924,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1969,1995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="384">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[874,948,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="384">segreg</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis box="[1016,1117,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="384">acanthus</emphasis>
, referring to the free spineshaped distal process of the sacculus.
</paragraph>
